page.title: 13Housing, Dunnington/Murton
page.content: The old houses in Dunnington date back to about 1750, we think, and are on the two main streets. There are a few more recent houses, in the same old brick,which have been inserted in these streets. Most of the houses in the village have been built in the last twenty years and are made of creamy coloured or red brick, with pantile roofs. Lower juniors house survey:- 37 of them live in detached houses, 22 in semi-detached bungalows and one in a terrace house, all owner-occupied. There are 40 council houses in Dunnington. There are 12 farm houses in the D block. Murton has a considerable proportion of older houses, with a bit of in-filling, and one small estate.
